{
  "stem": "14613.6",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But one day when we arrived to Bergen-Belsen, we met a girl, a young lady, whom we knew from before the war.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she was a friend of our sister, the oldest sister, Dasza.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So of course, the normal question, did you meet my sisters?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And she told us, yes, I did.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were in Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they left a few days ago, because one of your sisters is very sick.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Swedish government took or is taking a few thousand sick people to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they're are sending them to sanatoriums, to see if they can do something to improve their health.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And because this one sister was sick, the other sister went with her, since the Swedish government did not want to separate them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were told that they went to Bremerhaven, to Lubeck, which was not far from there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they were supposed to go the next day or day after to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now having heard that, that of course gave us some extra wings.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we went to the British military police to ask them for a special permit to travel that night, to go to Lubeck.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I cannot forget the British captain who was in charge of the so-called permits or whatever it is.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He was a heavy set guy, sitting behind the desk.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And after listening to us as to what we wanted to do, his only answer was look, late, it's too late.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You cannot travel at night.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You have to wait until tomorrow.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Of course, we were not too happy with the reply.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we told him in no uncertain terms, whether you want to or not, whether you give us the permit or not, we are going to go to Lubeck at night.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
